<title>USA: Medford Bank to reorganize into holding co.</title>
<headline>Medford Bank to reorganize into holding co.</headline>
<dateline>MEDFORD, Mass. 1997-05-28</dateline>
<text>
<p>Medford Bank said on Wednesday it will reorganize itself into a holding company structure so it has greater flexibility to expand.</p>
<p>The company said in a news release that its shareholders, if they approve the change, would exchange their bank stock for shares in the new holding company.</p>
<p>Medford is a savings bank with more than $1 billion in assets. Its shares were down 1/2 to 27 in late morning Nasdaq trading.</p>
